article.headline: Norfolk State 69, Bethune Cookman 49
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Calvin Brown had 25 points, leading four Norfolk State players in double figures in the Spartans' 69-49 win over Bethune-Cookman Monday night. Brown shot 9-of-13 from the floor as Norfolk State (10-10, 8-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) grabbed the lead early and never trailed. Karandick Ogunride and Chakowby Hicks each added 13 points for the Spartans while Tony Murphy finished with 10. Antonio Webb led the Wildcats (9-12, 6-6) with 12 points, and was the only Bethune-Cookman player in double figures. Webb hit a 3-pointer to open the second half and cut Norfolk State's lead to 32-26, but the Spartans then used a 17-4 run to put the game out of reach. The Wildcats never got closer than 10 points again.
